Undid revision 946081243 by [[Special:Contributions/Dibbydib|Dibbydib]] ([[User talk:Dibbydib|talk]]) I did not publish the source in question. What are you talking about?

If the conclusion of the study is not a primary source, then none of it is (except the raw data, which is not what my edit is based on). The conclusion is in partial contradiction to the results summary and to the rest of the paper itself, which clearly states that there are measurable neurological differences in those who were exposed to thimerosal in early age. The experience level of editors (one of which is you) is irrelevant to this.
